# Overview

Dineros.cc is a predictive budgeting and financial management platform. It combines a Nuxt 4 web app, a Nitro/H3 server with REST endpoints, a forecasting engine, integrations (Plaid, Alchemy), and background processing. The repository is a PNPM workspace with two packages:

- app/ — primary Nuxt application (UI + API + services + Prisma schema, tests)
- microservice/ — companion H3 service for specialized ops (notably field-encryption migrations / key rotation)

Key product capabilities (derived from code paths and tests):
- Account registers and entries with forecasting and snapshots
- Budgets, categories (hierarchical), savings goals
- Bills (profiles and instances), reconciliation periods
- Plaid bank sync (items, link flows, webhooks, sync logs)
- Crypto wallet tracking via Alchemy (EVM chains, token balances)
- Notifications and admin audit/logging
- MFA (email codes, TOTP, passkeys)

## Tech stack

- Frontend: Nuxt 4, Vue 3, Pinia, Tailwind CSS
- Server: Nitro/H3 (Nuxt server), TypeScript
- Data: Prisma ORM, MySQL 8 (Decimal for money), Redis
- Background: BullMQ (queues), nuxt-cron (cron under app/server/cron)
- Integrations: Plaid, Postmark, OpenAI (logging), Alchemy (EVM)
- Tooling: Vitest, Playwright, ESLint, PNPM, Docker
- Deploy: Docker images to GCR; GKE manifests in .deploy/

## Audience and use

- Maintainers and contributors: extend features, fix bugs, evolve schema/services
- AI agents (Cursor): follow project rules under .cursor/rules/* and skills under .cursor/skills/*
- Ops: build, ship, and rotate keys using provided GitHub Actions and k8s templates

## Quick start (local)

- Copy env: cp .env.example .env
- Start DB/Redis: docker compose up -d
- Generate Prisma: pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate
- Run dev: pnpm dev (Nuxt on http://localhost:3000)
- Tests: pnpm test (Vitest), pnpm test:e2e (Playwright)

Notes:
- Database is MySQL 8. Prisma schema lives at app/prisma/schema.prisma
- Some tests require prisma generate; CI does this explicitly
